sql:
SELECT p.patient_id, p.age
FROM patients p
JOIN adverse_events ae ON p.patient_id = ae.patient_id;

external_knowledge:
Frequent visitors are patients who have visited more than once. Key health indicators include CRP levels and disease activity scores, which are critical for assessing patient health and disease progression.;
"Frequent" in this context means patients who have at least two recorded visits. CRP stands for C-reactive protein, which is a marker of inflammation. Disease activity scores are used to measure the severity of a patient’s condition.;
Age and gender are important demographic factors that can influence the interpretation of health indicators and disease activity scores.;

sql:
SELECT patients.age, patients.gender, patients.ethnicity 
FROM patients 
INNER JOIN baseline_data ON patients.baseline_id = baseline_data.baseline_id;

external_knowledge:
- "mature smokers" refers to those older than 50 and currently smoking;
- "initial check-ups" refer to baseline data;
- "follow-up visits" refer to subsequent visit data;
- "notably high" CRP levels mean above 1.5;
- Grouping by age and gender allows for analysis of CRP variations within these demographics.

sql:
SELECT p.age, p.gender
FROM patients p
INNER JOIN baseline_data b ON p.baseline_id = b.baseline_id;

